Text: The economic impact of the now five-day long UAW strike of General Motors Co. is mounting  -  and expected to rise as the strike ripples through the supply base. Striking GM union members, laid-off temporary workers and suppliers workers linked to GM production are losing an estimated $9.3 million per day, according to an analysis released by East Lansing-based Anderson Economic Group.
